Business Brief -- Evans  Sutherland Computer:
   Quarterly Net Rose 3.8%;
   Year's Earnings Fell 43%
For its fourth quarter, the company posted net income of
$4 million, or 46 cents a share, on sales of $39.3 million,
compared with year-earlier net income of $3.9 million, or 44
cents a share, on sales of $43.2 million. The most recent
quarter included an extraordinary gain of $393,000.
   For the year, Evans  Sutherland posted net income of
$10.7 million, or $1.21 a share, compared with year-earlier
net income of $16.6 million, or $1.84 a share. The 1991
results include an extraordinary gain of $1.3 million from
the repurchase of convertible debentures. Sales for the year
dropped 8% to $144.9 million, from $157.6 million.
   Evans  Sutherland said net in its 1992 first and second
quarters will be "substantially below" 1991 levels. In the
year-earlier first quarter, the company posted net income of
$1.1 million, or 13 cents a share, on sales of $35.8 million.
In the year-ago second quarter, Evans posted net income of
$3.3 million, or 37 cents a share, on sales of $39.2 million.